oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Central Fire Station in Jackson
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of Central Fire Station, formerly located on North Church Street in Jackson. Groups of unidentified firemen pose with two fire trucks that are parked partially in the street. Handwriting at the bottom of the photograph reads: "Central Fire Station, North Church Street, Jackson, Tennessee, 1927."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Fire stations; Fire engines; Fire fighters
